{{Infobox film | name = Aphrodite Superstar | image = Afrodite Superstar Cover.jpg | image_size = | border = | alt = | caption = The video cover for ''Afrodite Superstar'' | director = [[Venus Hottentot]] | producer = [[Candida Royalle]] | writer = | screenplay = | story = | based on = <!-- {{based on|title of the original work|writer of the original work}} --> | narrator = | starring = | music = | cinematography = | editing = | studio = | distributor = | released = {{Film date|2007|||New School for Social Research}}<!-- {{Film date|Year|Month|Day|Location}} --> | runtime = | country = | language = | budget = | gross = }}
'''''Afrodite Superstar''''' is an American [[Independent film|independent]] [[art film]] shot in [[New York City]] in 2006. The film has also been referred to as [[erotica]]. The director also refers to the film as an [[experimental film]] as the characters break the [[fourth wall]], and there is a blend of satire. ''Afrodite Superstar'' was [[Film director|directed]] by [[Venus Hottentot]]. [[Executive producer]] [[Candida Royalle]] is also credited with directing the sexual scenes. ''Afrodite Superstar'' has been endorsed by [[American Association of Sexual Educators, Counselors and Therapists]] and [[premiere]]d in 2007 at the [[New School for Social Research]]<ref>[http://www.eros-zine.com/articles/2007-03-06/afrodite_superstar0306/ Afrodite Superstar, Afrodite Exposed, Sexual Empowerment in an Adult Hip Hop Film, Afrodite Superstar, Abiola Abrams, Venus Hottentot, Candida Royalle, Natasha Cortes, Simone Valentino, India, Mr. Marcus, Justin Long, Sativa Verte, Jay Junker, Liliana Vel] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080723141923/http://www.eros-zine.com/articles/2007-03-06/afrodite_superstar0306/ |date=July 23, 2008 }}</ref> with a discussion about women of color and sexual images. The film subsequently screened as part of an art exhibit called ''Hos, Putas and Dragon Ladies: Our Sexuality Remixed'' at the [[Chashama|chashama Gallery]] in [[Manhattan]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.chashama.org/dale/eventdisplay.php?id=2356; |title=this citation is provided to verify the exhibit, but does not include reference to the film. |access-date=2007-12-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071224132043/http://www.chashama.org/dale/eventdisplay.php?id=2356 |archive-date=2007-12-24 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref> ''Afrodite Superstar'' was nominated for 7 [[AVN Awards]] in 2007 including "Best Director", "Best Screenplay" and "Best Musical Score." The film was referred to as "erotic" and "cerebral" in ''[[Essence Magazine]]'',<ref>[http://www.essence.com/essence/bodyandsoul/relationships/0,16109,1640516,00.html Try This At Home : Essence.com<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071224181608/http://www.essence.com/essence/bodyandsoul/relationships/0%2C16109%2C1640516%2C00.html |date=2007-12-24 }}</ref> and was mentioned in the [[Village Voice]]'s 2007 Sexy Gift Guide<ref>{{cite web|author=Tristan Taormino |url=http://www.villagevoice.com/people/0749,taormino,78549,24.html |title=> people > Pucker Up: Eighth Annual Sexy Gift Guide by Tristan Taormino |publisher=village voice |date=2007-11-27 |accessdate=2011-11-11 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080724011905/http://www.villagevoice.com/people/0749%2Ctaormino%2C78549%2C24.html |archivedate=2008-07-24 }}</ref> by sexpert [[Tristan Taormino]].
==Plot==
The satirical film spoofs several recent pop cultural [[It Girl]] moments such as Janet Jackson's wardrobe malfunction and Ashlee Simpson's lip synching fiasco. It has also been called an African American ''[[Red Shoe Diaries]]''.{{citation needed |date=March 2013}}
==Director== {{Off topic |Venus Hottentot |section |date=March 2013}}
''Afrodite Superstar'' was directed by art filmmaker [[Venus Hottentot]].
Venus Hottentot is a feminist art school graduate who wanted to make a film that showed positive sexual representations of women of color to directly contrast the images in pop culture music videos, films and magazines, while also employing comedy and satire. She chose the name Venus Hottentot to reclaim the spirit of a South African woman, also called [[Saartjie Baartman]], who was sexually displayed and exploited in Europe. The film quotes [[Gloria Steinem]] and [[bell hooks]], and the director has been called the [[Zane (erotica author)|Zane]] of filmmaking. Venus Hottentot does not use the word "porn" to describe ''Afrodite Superstar'' as this term is misleading for this film.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.edenfantasys.com/sex-toy-reviews/media/afrodite-superstar |title=Sex toys reviews – AfroDite Superstar - Erotic video - Erotic and educational media |publisher=Edenfantasys.com |date=2007-06-29 |accessdate=2011-11-11}}</ref> To this end, the film has drawn ire from those seeking to use it for pornographic purposes as porn/ audience arousal was not the director's mission.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.podcastdirectory.com/podshows/index.php?sid=1458607 |title=TruMix.com : PodcastDirectory.com : Professor P's P4NORAMA Podcast |publisher=PodcastDirectory.com |date=2007-07-04 |accessdate=2011-11-11}}</ref> As an [[African American]] filmmaker, her objective with this project was reclaiming the voice and expression of women of color, as well as raising sexual self-esteem.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.venushottentot.com |title=Afrodite Superstar |publisher=Venushottentot.com |date= |accessdate=2011-11-11}}</ref>
Venus Hottentot has been identified as TV host/novelist and art film maker [[Abiola Abrams]].<ref>[http://www.abiolaabrams.com/id54.html Abiola Abrams' Film Page] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080531154226/http://www.abiolaabrams.com/id54.html |date=May 31, 2008 }}</ref>
