{{Infobox artwork | title = Eagles and Prey | image_file = File:Central Park NYC - Eagles and Prey Sculpture by Christophe Fratin - IMG 5715.JPG | caption = The sculpture in 2010 | painting_alignment = | image_size = | alt = | other_language_1 = | other_title_1 = | other_language_2 = | other_title_2 = | artist = [[Christophe Fratin]] | catalogue = | year = {{start date|1850}} | type = Sculpture | material = Bronze | subject = | height_metric = | width_metric = | length_metric = | height_imperial = | width_imperial = | length_imperial = | diameter_metric = | diameter_imperial = | dimensions = | dimensions_ref = | metric_unit = cm<!--don't leave blank—either don't include it, or include the default cm. --> | imperial_unit = in<!--don't leave blank—either don't include it, or include the default in. --> | condition = | city = [[New York City]], [[New York (state)|New York]], United States | museum = | accession = | pushpin_map = Manhattan | pushpin_mapsize = | pushpin_map_caption = Location in New York City | pushpin_label_position = | coordinates = {{coord|40.77167|-73.97308|display=inline,title}} | owner = | url = <!--{{URL|example.com}} Only for official web pages--> }} '''''Eagles and Prey''''' is an outdoor [[bronze sculpture]] by Christophe Fratin, located in [[Central Park]] in [[Manhattan]], [[New York (state)|New York]]. Created in 1850 and installed in Central Park in 1863, it is the oldest known sculpture in any New York City park.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nycgovparks.org/parks/centralpark/monuments/427|title=Central Park: Eagles and Prey|accessdate=June 14, 2014|publisher=[[New York City Department of Parks and Recreation]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.centralparknyc.org/things-to-see-and-do/attractions/eagles-and-prey.html|title=Eagles and Prey|accessdate=June 14, 2014|publisher=[[Central Park Conservancy]]}}</ref>
